ANTHRAX - KYRGYZSTAN (02): (TALAS) HUMAN, CATTLE, WOAH
******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 21 Jul 2022
Source: WOAH-WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System) 2022 [edited]
https://wahis.woah.org/#/report-info?reportId=57395


Anthrax, Kyrgyzstan
--------------
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 15 Jul 2022
Confirmed: 18 Jul 2022
Ended: 18 Jul 2022
Reported: 21 Jul 2022
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence in a zone or a compartment
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location: Kok-Say village, Kara-Buura, Talas
Started: 15 Jul 2022
Ended: 18 Jul 2022
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Cattle / 2 / 1 / 0 / 1 / 0 / 500
Affected population: Two susceptible cows were in the same yard. In the whole village there were about 500 cows and other animals.

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: According to the results of laboratory research, anthrax bacilli were isolated and 4 people fell ill.

Domestic control measures applied: disinfection; movement control; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; quarantine; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); surveillance within the restricted zone

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type: National center for veterinary diagnosis, Bichkek (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / Smears evaluation / 18 Jul 2022 / positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the WOAH report at the source URL above.]

